<p>Top-tier Barolos from legendary producers like Giacomo Conterno, Bruno Giacosa, and Giuseppe Mascarello can age gracefully for <strong>30-50+ years</strong>. Mid-tier traditional producers typically peak at 15-25 years, while modern-style Barolos from quality estates reach their prime in 8-15 years due to softer extraction techniques.</p>

